  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 4.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Against whom do ye sport yourselves?",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " The idolatrous Israelites here addressed, no doubt, made a mock of the few righteous who were still living among them, and vexed their souls, as his fellow-towns-men did the soul of \"just Lot\" (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Peter 2:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). They \"made wide the mouth\" at them, and \"drew out the tongue\" in derision (comp. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 22:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 35:21",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). The prophet asks, \"Against whom do ye do this? Is it not rather against God, whose servants these men are, than against them?\" ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Are",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "ye not children of transgression?",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " rather, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "are ye not",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "yourselves",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "children of apostasy",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "? ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "and therefore more truly objects of scorn than they",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "? ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "A",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "cmt_word",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "A",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "seed of falsehood.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Idols were viewed by Isaiah as \"lies\" (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Isaiah 45:20",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Romans 1:25",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Revelation 22:15",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). Idolaters were therefore \"a seed of falsehood\" - men who put their trust in a lie. Isaiah 57:4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
